gomodel:SYNGO_1900  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains 1264 proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation). The poly (A) - binding protein is among these identified proteins, it is an ubiquitiously expressed protein that binds to poly(A) tails of mRNA. PABP interaction partners like PAIP2A are involved in the control of synaptic plasticity (Khoutorsky et al., 2013, PMID 23622065).\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- Listed as \"Poly(A)-binding protein 1 (PABP 1)\" in Table.S1. Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1900" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

